<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1408,2009]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Body dorsally dark castaneous with some metallic green shine on pronotum and corium. Ventrally castaneous to dark castaneous and shiny but without iridescent color; abdomen with three longitudinal clear bands. Head in front of eyes reddish to castaneous. Fourth and fifth antennal segments missing. Anterolateral margins of pronotum rugose, with long yellowish stripe on each reaching base of each humeral angle. Metapleuron with distal reddish spot. Metasternal process reddish, branches divergent, curved and evanescent; anterior bifurcation almost completely excavated leaving free part of branches long (
<figureCitation box="[745,882,1805,1829]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,217,1071]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1079]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15, Edessa splendens sp. nov. 10 – 12, male, pygophore; 10, dorsal view; 11, posterior view; 12, ventral view. 13, Female, genital plates. 14 – 15, Metasternal process; 15, lateral view; 16, ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205149/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Figs. 
<number box="[809,882,1805,1829]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1408,2009]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[373,511,1841,1865]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,217,1071]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1079]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15, Edessa splendens sp. nov. 10 – 12, male, pygophore; 10, dorsal view; 11, posterior view; 12, ventral view. 13, Female, genital plates. 14 – 15, Metasternal process; 15, lateral view; 16, ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205149/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Figs. 
<number box="[437,511,1841,1865]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Base of posterolateral angles of pygophore slightly tumid. Process of genital cup long, reaching dorsal rim. Ventral rim widely excavated leaving parameres visible in ventral view; lobes large and acuminate close to and below level of posterolateral angle. Paramere large, smooth, with long narrow lobe laterally directed reaching tumid area of posterolateral angle and another large, long, narrow, and rounded projected anteriorly reaching dorsal rim. Segment X with posterior face truncate and uneven.
</paragraph>
