<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1197,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,333,1341,1366]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is recognizable by the lack of iridescent color on the head, scutellum, and ventral surface. The shape of gonocoxites 
<number box="[505,521,1377,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="8.0">8</number>
, pygophore, and parameres are also diagnostic.
</paragraph>
